<br>
1)  This writer (Leslie Walker) evidently worked hard on her writing to keep it objective and factual, qualifying each of her remarks or opinions as she went.  For example, when she said &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>these games are still so darn hard to learn</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->...&quot;, she qualified that by mentioning she had only tried Planetside to base her opinion on.<br>
<br>
2)  When she said &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I don't see them being ready for the mass market quite yet</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;, I believe she was referring to a &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>high-tech conference</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; that had been discussing &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>the growing number of other 'massively multi-player online games' represent an entirely new media type, one they believe is on the verge of the mass market</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;  In that context, it does appear that Everquest itself is not quite yet mass marketed.<br>
<br>
